overview: The user initiated a request to enhance the aesthetic appeal of their
  sleep questionnaire application, which they described as "a little donkey" in
  terms of style. The assistant conducted a thorough review of the existing
  design, identifying a generic color palette, plain layouts, and basic UI
  components. The approach involved a comprehensive redesign, starting with a
  new sleep-themed color palette using deep indigos, purples, and teal accents.
  Key components like the main form layout, progress bar, intro section,
  checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards were all updated with a more
  polished and cohesive look. All questionnaire sections and the report section
  were consistently themed. Additionally, a console error related to
  values being passed to input fields was diagnosed and fixed by ensuring
  values were converted to empty strings in the  component. The
  conversation concluded with the user requesting further refinements to alert
  colors and border opacities based on the assistant's aesthetic review.
